{"key":"post-10985047","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10985047</id>\n<content>If you want to soak substrate trays, simply place them in a clean sink with the drain open.&amp;nbsp; Allow the faucet to slowly run until it fills the tray and begins to run over.&amp;nbsp; Let it slowly overflow for an hour or two and then dump out any water that hasn't absorbed.&amp;nbsp; Cakes soak for 12 to 24 hours, but that's too long for bulk substrates.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I've tried the tubing idea several times and every single time it caused green molds.&amp;nbsp; The molds travel through the tubing when there's not water in it and then they get to the center of the substrate where they wreck havoc.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10985336</next>\n<prev>10984984</prev>\n<first>10984721</first>\n<last>10985336</last>\n<when>1251901204</when>\n<utime>09/02/09 05:20 PM</utime>\n</post>"}